article.description: Cam Ward scored 15 points and Vermont rolled past Fisher 84-37 on Saturday.
article.headline: Vermont rolls past NAIA-member Fisher College 84-37
article.linkText: Vermont rolls past NAIA-member Fisher College 84-37
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- Cam Ward scored 15 points and Vermont rolled past Fisher 84-37 on Saturday. Ward was 6 of 7 from the field, including three 3-pointers. Dylan Sinnickson also had three from the arc and finished with career highs of 11 points and 12 rebounds for his first double-double. Drew Urquhart was the third player off the bench in double figures with 10 points. Starter Kurt Steidl also had 10 points, all in the first half when the Catamounts (6-6) took a 46-18 lead. Vermont made just under 50 percent of their shots, sank 13 3-pointers and outrebounded Fisher 51-30. The Falcons (5-7), an NAIA Division II team from Boston, were simply no match, shooting just 20 percent and making only 1 of 17 3-point tries. Tyler Shular was their leading scorer with 12. They did make 14 of their 17 free throws.
